200
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,670
to a known good point in time.

201
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:59,040
And the challenge, as we all know,

202
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,870
is that every single partition

203
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:05,160
can have a different last good known copy.

204
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:09,000
And then number two,
you need to also ensure

205
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,540
that the reconfiguration
at the application level

206
00:09:11,540 --> 00:09:14,250
is as little as possible.

207
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,420
Because you don't have to deal

208
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:17,020
with reconfiguring the application

209
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:19,830
to talk to a different DynamoDB instance.

210
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:22,983
And that can be a
time-consuming operation.

211
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:26,400
Number three, of course, TCL.

212
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,500
You need to ensure that the resources

213
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:32,220
that you end up spending to
get the app back up online

214
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:34,920
is as minimal as possible.

215
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:38,070
And finally, you need to ensure
the best user experience,

216
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:40,620
which means little to no downtime.

217
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:43,680
And we don't want Sharon to get frustrated

218
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,723
