228
00:10:10,590 --> 00:10:13,740
And mind you, this is for
each and every partition

229
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:16,620
that's impacted, you'll
have to do a full restore.

230
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:19,200
And then you need to
cherry-pick the pieces

231
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,960
for each partition from the full restores,

232
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,580
copy it back to the source table

233
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:26,880
so that you don't have to
reconfigure the application

234
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:29,070
at a later point in time.

235
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:31,860
And finally, delete all
the temporary tables

236
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:33,480
that you've created.

237
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:37,280
And finally, I want to mention
that you have to do this

238
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:40,470
over and over again for
every single partition

239
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:42,240
that's impacted.

240
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:44,130
If you have 1,000 partitions impacted,

241
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:45,840
you'll have to do this 1,000 times.

242
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,580
Now imagine that.

243
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:48,963
That's recovery hell.

244
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:54,420
And now, let's take a
look at how simple it is

245
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:58,140
