249
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:09,750
hit recover, and that's about it.

250
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:14,010
It recovers only what's needed
for every single partition

251
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,560
to the point in time that you've selected

252
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,180
and directly to the source table

253
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:21,900
so you don't have to reconfigure
the application at all.

254
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:25,470
And step number two, there is no step two.

255
00:11:25,470 --> 00:11:28,320
Simple as that, all right?

